    {
      "type": "river",
      "trigger": "after_stop",
      "triggerStop": 3,
      "title": "The Framework Data River!",
      "text": "You reach a wide river of data. The framework-trails file is over three thousand lines. How does the game match quiz events to the right difficulty tier for each player?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "The player picks a profession at setup — Ralph Wiggum sees easy, Vibe Coder sees easy plus medium, Engineer sees medium plus hard, Staff Architect sees hard only — and the game filters events by those tiers",
          "correct": true,
          "explanation": "That's the system. Four professions map to different difficulty tier combinations. The game filters the fifteen events per framework down to the matching tiers. Fortune events bypass the filter and trigger on answer streaks regardless."
        },
        {
