        },
        {
          "text": "Always use bullet points, keep paragraphs under 100 words, and include line numbers when referencing code",
          "correct": false,
          "explanation": "These are documentation conventions, not TTS narration rules. The narration skill specifically targets spoken output. Bullet points don't help speech. The actual rules focus on sentence length, path pronunciation, and avoiding literal code reading."
        },
        {
          "text": "Use formal technical language, spell out every variable name, and include file paths in every sentence",
          "correct": false,
          "explanation": "The narration skill explicitly says to be conversational, not formal. Variable names should be described by purpose, not spelled out. And while file paths are mentioned, the key rule is to say 'slash' for separators and keep them natural. The focus is WHY, not WHAT."
        }
      ],
      "concept": "Shell Infrastructure",
      "difficulty": "hard"
